$ Visual Studio Code: User data directory
@ user data directory

The default location of the *user data directory* of → development/editors/Visual-Studio-Code is dependent on the platform:
table { ll
  `→ Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/Code/User[%APPDATA%\Code]` ☰ → Windows
  `$HOME\.config\Code` ☰ → Linux
  `$HOME\Library\Application Support\Code` ☰ macOS
table }

A custom location can be chosen with the → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-VS-Code/bin/code[`code` command line option] `--user-data-dir`.

The arguably most interesting subdirectory of the user data directory is `User` which stores files such as
  • `→ development/editors/Visual-Studio-Code/directories/user-data/User/keybindings_json`
  • `→ development/editors/Visual-Studio-Code/settings_json`
  • `storage.json`
